boundary condition

0 = inlet
(use rho,u,v,p)

1 = outlet
(don't use all values)

2 = slip wall
3 = non-slip wall
(don't use all values)

4 = symmetric conditions
(don't use all values)

5 = inlet for O grid
(use rho,u,v,p)
6 = inlet for O grid
(use rho,u,v,T)

7 = non-slip isothermal wall
(use T)